cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CR 

This paper is about testing the performance of the Apache Accumulo database using data from the Graph500 benchmark. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases). The paper also discusses the use of supercomputing techniques such as distributed arrays, domain decomposition, adaptive load balancing, and single-program-multiple-data programming, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.NI (networking and internet architecture), and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
